        public static final InjectableProperties DN_TO_SCHEMA_MAPPING
        Provides a mapping from the current request's base DN to the IDDM schema object type associated within that DN.

        For example, given an IDDM schema called "northwind" with a table called "App.Employees" and a naming context "table=employees,o=northwind" configured to show "App.Employees" objects, the ReadOnlyProperties entry returned by this method will contain the mapping: {"table=employees,o=northwind": "App.Employees"}.

        This property is most often used with SCHEMAS to retrieve the specific Schema and SchemaObjects used by the naming context.

      • PRIMARY_KEY_ATTRIBUTES

        public static final InjectableProperties PRIMARY_KEY_ATTRIBUTES
        Provides access to the attributes and values used to form an entry's primary key.

        For example, given a schema object created through IDDM's Context Builder where the primary key is made up of "title", "givenName", and "sn" attributes, an LDAP entry might look like: user=President George Washington,ou=presidents,o=people. The ReadOnlyProperties provides by this property will contain the attribute names and used to generate the RDN:

        {"givenName": "George", "sn": "Washington", "title": "President"}

        This property can be useful when needing to parse a custom primary key.

      • TARGET_SCHEMA_OBJECTS

        public static final InjectableProperties TARGET_SCHEMA_OBJECTS
        Specifies the types of objects that should be searched based on base DN of incoming search request.

        If IDDM searches a subtree containing multiple object types (e.g., Users, Groups), then IDDM will perform a unique search for each object type then aggregate the results. So this property is almost ways (if not always) going to have a single value.

        For example: {"names": ["APP.EMPLOYEES", "APP.SHIPPERS", "APP.ORDERS"]}
